elines for how to build better enterprises while simultaneously alleviating poverty. He outlines three key components that must be integrated to achieve results: the lived experiences of enterprises to date-both successes and failures; the development of an ecosystem that is conducive to market creation; and the voices of the poor, so that entrants can truly understand what poverty alleviation is about. London provides aspiring market leaders and their stakeholders with the tools and techniques needed to succeed in the unique, opportunity-rich BoP.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aBusiness planningxDeveloping countries. 0aBusiness planningzDeveloping countries. 0aIndustrial managementxDeveloping countries. 0aIndustrial managementzDeveloping countries. 0aLow-income consumersxDeveloping countriesxDeveloping countries. 0aLow-income consumerszDeveloping countries. 0aMarketsxDeveloping countries. 0aMarketszDeveloping countries. 0aPovertyxDeveloping countries. 0aPovertyzDeveloping countries. 0aSocial entrepreneurshipxDeveloping countries. 0aSocial entrepreneurshipzDeveloping countries. 0aSuccess in businessxDeveloping countries. 0aSuccess in businesszDeveloping countries. 4aBase of the Pyramid. 4aBoP frameworks. 4aBoP impact enterprise. 4aBoP promise. 4aBoP value propositions. 4aBoP. 4abottom of the pyramid. 4amaking profits while alleviating poverty. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Strategic Planning.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311070397940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080479733740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804797337423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804797337.jpg  a978-3-11-070397-9  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles